<head>AMBUSH</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>SURPRISE ATTACK</item>
<item>TRAP</item>
<item>ARCHAIC AMBUSCADE</item>
    </list>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">埋伏</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>ATTACK AND HIDE WHILE PREPARING to do so.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>[[COMMON/RARE]]</p>
<p>[GENERAL/SPECIFIC]</p>
<p>1. The current word for lying in ambush as part of attacking someone furtively in any context, formaly military or otherwise, is fú 伏.</p>
<p>[GENERAL]; [[COMMON]]</p>
<p>2. Fù 覆 is used as a military technical term limited to the use of ambushes in formal military campaigns.</p>
<p>[SPECIFIC]; [[RARE]]</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>埋伏</p>
